<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n26267h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n26" href="#n26267h">N26 (VI.B.18)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n26all.htm#n26267h"> 267(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ius vitae necisque / adrogation / adoption</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Institutions of the Private Law. Patria potestas]</font>&mdash;&hellip; according to the old formula recited in <mark>that sort of adoption known as adrogation</mark>, <font color="green">[the house-father]</font> had over <font color="green">[his children]</font> the power of life and death, <i><mark>jus vitae necisque</mark></i>. <small> &ldquo;ROMAN LAW&rdquo; <a name="EBRL2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBRL2"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 530</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
